      {
        "id": "16bfa231812fdb534b4cbfdc1c6ee4d978a039ba",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 1303,
          "name": "Junfeng Wang ",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "junfeng.a.wang@ericsson.com",
          "username": "JunfengWang"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-11-30 15:53:45.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nThe section that fix was added is for the existing behavior before “StndDefined” domain introduced. I wonder if the rules for eventId  is applicable to the “stndDefined” event, because the 3GPP payload shall be used to identify the event Id etc information. Perhaps we could add eventId rules for “stndDefined” separately",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "ee611b1db64dd13db105644b058a8d66d36a8d8f",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 5597,
          "name": "Damian Nowak",
          "display_name": "Damian Nowak",
          "email": "damian.nowak@nokia.com",
          "username": "deen1985"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2020-12-01 15:19:18.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n(2 comments)\n\nA response to Oskar`s comments.\nI`ll remove the section related to expected xNF/Analytis behaviors, and we go from there.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "d9bd245c3c5749e6e4e7eaf9acb84b115981359e",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 5597,
          "name": "Damian Nowak",
          "display_name": "Damian Nowak",
          "email": "damian.nowak@nokia.com",
          "username": "deen1985"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2020-12-01 15:22:51.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n> \n> The section that fix was added is for the existing behavior before “StndDefined” domain introduced. I wonder if the rules for eventId  is applicable to the “stndDefined” event, because the 3GPP payload shall be used to identify the event Id etc information. Perhaps we could add eventId rules for “stndDefined” separately\n\nWell, I think, we decided to decouple VES CommonHeader from stndDefinedFields.data.\nI agree, that 3GPP has mechanisms to identify the eventId, but I`ll keep these two things separate.\nFrom that perspective, I would like to avoid defining rules for stndDefined and other domains.\nIf we follow on this, we might start to define different rules for different domains finally, concerning the same fields, making the entire spec difficult to understand and follow.\n\nThus my vote would be to have a common rule on eventId for all domains.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
